I don't have the correct setup here to run the test but maybe it is an issue / change in your nghttp binary.
Did you use a new version? I guess the following patch to the tests should fix this, but I am still not sure
if this is a failure on server side or with the test setup:

Index: test/pyhttpd/nghttp.py
===================================================================
--- test/pyhttpd/nghttp.py	(revision 1918546)
+++ test/pyhttpd/nghttp.py	(working copy)
@@ -224,7 +224,7 @@
         if 0 == r.exit_code:
             lines = re.findall(r'[^\n]*\n', r.stdout, re.MULTILINE)
             for lidx, l in enumerate(lines):
-                m = re.match(r'\s*(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+/(.*)', l)
+                m = re.match(r'\s*(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+(\S+)\s+/*(/.*)', l)
                 if m:
                     assets.append({
                         "path": m.group(7),


